    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-05T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-05T18:00:00-05:00" n="655"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d655">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Stam, John C/47: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-05T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 5, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Your 26, January 17, 8 p.m. and despatch No. 3234, January 4,<note n="80"
                        xml:id="d655fn80">Despatch not printed.</note> the last received. Please
                    send by naval radio a summary of the steps taken and the results attained to
                    date by the Chinese Government as a consequence of the Stam murder and a
                    statement of the Legation’s opinion whether the action taken by the Chinese
                    Government is all that might reasonably be expected in the circumstances. Has
                    the Chinese Government given any acceptable assurances that any persons
                    connected with the murder have been punished?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
